Description: Rectangular strip of ivory inlay: broken off at one end, decorated with vertical incised lines. The strip is pierced by two holes, 0.3cm in diameter, at an interval of 3.5cm. The reverse side is flat and smooth.
Curator's comments: For pieces with the same pattern, see W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' II, pls.XXXVII, 52-3; XL, 51, 53, 55; XLI, 63-4; XLII, 1-5, 39-40; P. Montet, 'Kêmi' 8 (1946), pl.V. Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' II, pl.XLII, 38.
